<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Chicken Note</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="edn120">  120  The idea of a &lsquo;passionpallid nudity or plaguepurple nakedness&rsquo; tucked under the flap of an envelope cannot fail but put us in mind of Joyce's own private letters to Nora, pornographic tracts delivered in all innocence by an unsuspecting Catholic Irish postman. The writing and other marks on the envelope are discussed by <font face="wake">D</font> (Shaun) later in III.1 when answering the ninth query.  </div>
